bio.experienceSummary: I have been a babysitter and nanny to amazing families for 15 years. I have worked with children from infants to the ages of 13. I love kids and I love to watch them grow. I am very patient and loving. I have a 12-year-old daughter myself so I know the importance of nurturing, loving, and caring for kids. I have one goal and that is to keep a smile on the kids and parents faces that I provide my services too. Every family that I have worked for has been at least for 3+ and currently still will babysit for them when they need services. I assist with homework, fun activities, doctor visits, school pick ups, snack, light house work, and errands. I am currently working for an awesome family who relocating to another state , so unfortunately I am seeking new employment.

description.displayText:
Dani has been watching my two sons, ages 2 and 4, for 2 years now, since my youngest was 8 months old. She is so caring, loving, energetic, positive, and kind. She loves being busy with them and is always on-the-go. She takes them places like the zoo, library story time, gymnastics, playgrounds. I trust her driving my kids around. She is very dependable - always shows up on time. 

My kids love her, and I have loved Dani being a part of my family for the past 2 years. Any family would be lucky to have her help!

bio.experienceSummary: I'm a pretty good cook, as well as I'm really good with kids... I grew up in Jamaica, and I was always the designated babysitter in the family, so I have experience dealing with newborns straight up to teenagers. I have no issues helping out with light cleaning as well as cooking or pick ups ... I have my own transportation, and I love pets.

description.originalText: Responsible, trustworthy, experienced & reliable. She catered to our particular needs as parents as well as the individual needs of our 4 kids. Would absolutely recommend her to others and/or work with her again moving forwards!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi Parents! 

My name is Bruna and I'm 28yo and I've been working with kids since I was 15. As I am an older sister, I was always a natural caregiver. I have experience with kids from all ages including newborns.

I am a very calm, patient, polite, caring and loving person! I consider myself a good driver and I have a clean record. I am also CPR/First Aid certified and fully vaccinated. I can also provide references anytime if needed.

I love creating a connection with kids, see their milestones, teach them new things and help with their development. 

Understanding the parents/kids needs, affection, safety and respect are my priorities.

I also have experience as house manager, doing groceries, laundry, cooking meals and organizing stuff.

I am looking forward in hearing back from you and getting to know more about your family!

My name is Jessica , and I have had the pleasure of being a career nanny for 3 years. I am originally from a small town by the name of Aiken, located in the beautiful state of South Carolina.

I have had the pleasure of being an Early Childhood Educator since 2014. In the amount of time that I have been an early childhood educator, I can wholeheartedly say that I enjoy providing a safe, nurturing, and loving, environment for children of all ages. 

The majority of my time was spent being a lead teacher at Primrose School, in the infant program! I made my transition from the classroom, to nannying during the Covid19 pandemic. I enjoy teaching, nurturing, and having fun with all children!

description.displayText: Jessica was a nanny for our newborn for 4 months.  The only reason we didn't have her longer is because we actually already had a family friend nanny lined up to start but she wasn't available until August and we needed somebody to start in May.  I came on Care.com to find a temporary nanny and still can't believe how lucky we were to have found Jessica.  She was incredible with our baby.  She loved on him like he was her own and did awesome age-appropriate activities with him - even gave me suggestions on things to have at home for his activity time.  She was extremely punctual and flexible even when I suddenly would need to work extended hours in a given day.  She was such a genuinely kind and caring person and it was so incredibly hard on her last day with us.  She was such a blessing to our family. I would highly recommend Jessica.  She never called in sick, ways ALWAYS early and was just amazing with our child.  I love how she interacted with our baby and how much she helped us.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi family! I'm looking for a part time job starting July. 
I'm in school for an associate degree in nursing and in my free time I would love to help you out with your kids!
I'm a really happy, positive and proactive person. 
I have experience for 5 years with all the ages (even newborns!) and I have lots of references. I'm CPR certified and full vaccinated. I'm a strong driver and have my transportation. I speak Spanish if I that's plus. 
Kids will always feel safe and loved by me. 

Let me know if you are interested and would like to chat more!

description.originalText:
We would enthusiastically recommend Valentina to any family looking to have her as an addition and critical part of their daily routine.  She cared for our newborn son as well as our 4 and 6 year-old children with excellence.

Qualities that make Valentina a great nanny:
1.       Safety-conscious
2.      Honest, thorough and loving
3.      Great attitude and earnest worker
4.      Punctual
5.      Fun

Most of all, she is loved by our children and we never doubted our trust in her!

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as vibrant responsible & organized!

I like working with kids because I have three children. My entire family works in child care. 

I started working with kids when I started to substitute teach around 6 years ago.

In my spare time, I like to organize activities for my children.

One thing you should know about me is I am timely and respectful. I take pride in working with children.

I'm a caregiver with 12 years of experience, and my passion for childcare stems from my previous babysitting roles. I find great joy in positively impacting children's lives and supporting families by providing reliable care.

As a caregiver, patience, creativity, and friendliness are my strong suits. I believe in open communication with parents, whether it's through regular updates or at pickup, and I'm comfortable enforcing household rules.

I enjoy a variety of games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that enhance learning. I'm comfortable caring for up to three children of various ages, and my skills include first aid and CPR training.

I'm happy to assist with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, light housekeeping, and travel. I'm excited about the opportunity to provide your family with exceptional care and be a part of your children's growth.

description.displayText:
Such a blessing to our family!

- B. Family

bio.experienceSummary: Child care certification from New York. I have been in the childcare field since 1984 with additional skills. If you read my profile you will find that I am a mother of three a grandmother of three and cared for my elderly parents. Please feel free to ask any questions or concerns. I am a non-smoker and I have my own car.

description.displayText: AnneMarie is very loving, caring, and patient. Excellent with children and the elderly. A trustworthy, compassionate lady with a very good heart. I Would recommend her without hesitation.

bio.experienceSummary: I have been babysitting since the age of 12. With nine nieces and nephews, I had no choice but to love children. Babysitting and tutoring were my main sources of income in college. I have continued to babysit occasionally since graduated with a Bachelor's degree in Biology.

I've always been passionate about making a difference in the lives of children. As a patient and calm individual with over three years of childcare experience, I thrive in environments where I can nurture and support the growth and development of young minds. I believe in fostering open and honest communication with parents, providing regular updates about their child's day and promptly addressing any issues that may arise.

I am comfortable enforcing household rules while following the parents' guidance and preferences. My approach to childcare includes a variety of engaging activities, such as board games, puzzles, educational games, and technology-based games and apps, to ensure a well-rounded and enjoyable experience for the children in my care.

I am comfortable caring for one child at a time and have experience working with children of all ages, from infants to preteens. I hold some college education and am proficient in English.
